comments: Smart (BOS) makes marginal contact as he goes to, and not through, Garland (CLE) during his dribble in the post.
LeVert (CLE) makes marginal contact with Smart (BOS) during the shot attempt.
Brown (BOS) slightly extends his arm into Mobley (CLE) as Mobley is firming up to set the pick, and the contact is marginal.
Horford (BOS) and Mitchell (CLE) mutually engage and disengage as Mitchell moves around on the perimeter.
Horford (BOS) moves alongside Mitchell's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact that occurs on the driving shot attempt.
Garland (CLE) is moving alongside Brogdon's (BOS) path during his drive near the baseline, and incidental contact occurs after Brogdon passes.
Mitchell (CLE) delivers contact to Smart's (BOS) arm as he starts his upward shooting motion toward the rim.
Mitchell's (CLE) leg slightly drifts forward on his shot attempt, causing it to brush Brown (BOS) as he legally contests the jump shot attempt. The contact is marginal.
Mitchell (CLE) extends his resting forearm slightly into Tatum (BOS) during the driving shot attempt, and the contact is marginal.
Mobley (CLE) gets to ball height and cleanly deflects the ball from Horford (BOS) during the rebound attempt.
Brown (BOS) reaches in and delivers contact to Mitchell's (CLE) arm during his drive. The contact occurs on a drive that does not end up inside the LDB, and a personal foul is correctly assessed.
Garland (CLE) moves his pivot foot heel-to-toe to create distance prior to the foul.
Williams' (BOS) hand slides off the ball and onto Garland's (CLE) wrist on the perimeter.
As Allen (CLE) contests the driving shot attempt, marginal contact occurs with Tatum's (BOS) arm after he has released the ball on his dunk.
Tatum (BOS) makes marginal contact with Mitchell (CLE) as he spins off it on the perimeter.
Tatum (BOS) gets to ball height and cleanly blocks Mitchell's (CLE) shot attempt. Tatum then makes incidental "high-five" contact with Mitchell thereafter.
Williams (BOS) and Allen (CLE) mutually engage and disengage during the inbound.
Mitchell (CLE) and Smart (BOS) come together off-ball as Smart slips and loses his footing.
Garland (CLE) and Williams (BOS) mutually engage and disengage in the post.
Mobley (CLE) is set in Smart's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs as he releases to roll toward the basket.
Smart (BOS) grasps Mobley's (CLE) lower body as Horford (BOS) tips the ball out simultaneously during the rebound.
LeVert's (CLE) hand slides off the ball and makes contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm during his shot attempt.
Williams (BOS) initiates contact as he moves into Allen's (CLE) path and impedes his FOM off-ball.
Allen (CLE) extends both arms into Smart (BOS) to create space in the lane.
Mitchell (CLE) is moving alongside Smart (BOS) when marginal contact occurs as Smart enters his upward shooting motion.
Mobley (CLE) and Williams (BOS) mutually engage and disengage during the rebound attempt.
Garland (CLE) extends his arm toward Smart (BOS) as both players engage on the perimeter.
Smart (BOS) leans in as Garland (CLE) is already losing control of the ball on the perimeter. The body contact is marginal.
Brown (BOS) moves alongside Garland's (CLE) path and legally contests the shot attempt.
Williams (BOS) faces Allen (CLE) up and continues to hold him near the basket, impeding, and affecting his ability to pursue the rebound.
Wade (CLE) avoids making body contact with Brown (BOS) as he contests the jump shot attempt.
